HEADWORD: Tartness
<hw>Tart"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
tart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acrimony; sourness; keenness; poignancy;
severity; asperity; acerbity; harshness. See
<er>Acrimony</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tartralic</ent>⟦br⟧
